Here goes nothing...


27 Sep 2012 20:46






This one is a bit of an experiment which I quite honestly don't know if I've hit the sweet spot on. The inspiration came from a conversation in the SCP staff channel in which we discovered a little-known fact about bees: a queen bee is pampered and has her every need tended to an already-laid egg in preparation to produce a new resident queen. A few of us considered the horror if the queen were actually a sentient, sapient being and thus this idea came into being.

On a completely separate note, Mr Wilt has informed me that today is the first anniversary of Bee Day. Talk about coincidences







